cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SD

This paper is about a new domain adaptation method for Combinatory Categorial Grammar (CCG) parsing, which is a subfield of computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for parsing, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of existing benchmark datasets and the creation of new experimental datasets, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Sound).
